
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `curl` baraye ersal va daryaft dade az yek URL (manba’e resane interneti) estefade mishavad. Mesle download kardan file-ha az internet ya ferestadan etela’at be yek API (Application Programming Interface).

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `curl -O <URL>`  --> 💾 Download kardan file ba haman esm az URL.
    🔹 `curl -o <filename> <URL>` --> ✏️ Download kardan file va zakhire kardan an ba yek esme digar.
    🔹 `curl -I <URL>`  --> ℹ️ Namayesh header-haye HTTP faghat (etela’at meta).
    🔹 `curl -X <METHOD> <URL>` --> 📡 Estefade az yek method HTTP khass (mesle POST, PUT, DELETE).
    🔹 `curl -d <data> <URL>` --> 📤 Eesal data ba request HTTP POST.
    🔹 `curl -H "<Header: Value>" <URL>` --> ⚙️ Ezafe kardan header haye HTTP khass.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ curl -O https://example.com/myfile.txt

    🔹 Download kardan myfile.txt az example.com va zakhire kardan an ba haman esm.

    $ curl -o newfile.txt https://example.com/myfile.txt

    🔹 Download kardan myfile.txt az example.com va zakhire kardan an ba esme newfile.txt.

    $ curl -I https://example.com

    🔹 Namayesh header-haye HTTP az example.com.

    $ curl -X POST -d "name=John&age=30" https://example.com/api

    🔹 Eersal data be yek API ba estefade az method POST.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ curl https://example.com

    🔹 Download kardan HTML page az example.com va namayesh an dar terminal. Agar mikhayid zakhire konid az gozine `-O` ya `-o` estefade konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `curl` command is used to send and receive data from a URL (Uniform Resource Locator). It is commonly used to download files from the internet or send data to an API (Application Programming Interface).

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `curl -O <URL>`  --> 💾 Download a file from the URL, using the same filename.
    🔹 `curl -o <filename> <URL>` --> ✏️ Download a file and save it with a different filename.
    🔹 `curl -I <URL>`  --> ℹ️ Show only the HTTP headers (meta information).
    🔹 `curl -X <METHOD> <URL>` --> 📡 Use a specific HTTP method (e.g., POST, PUT, DELETE).
    🔹 `curl -d <data> <URL>` --> 📤 Send data with an HTTP POST request.
    🔹 `curl -H "<Header: Value>" <URL>` --> ⚙️ Add custom HTTP headers.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ curl -O https://example.com/myfile.txt

    🔹 Download myfile.txt from example.com and save it with the same name.

    $ curl -o newfile.txt https://example.com/myfile.txt

    🔹 Download myfile.txt from example.com and save it as newfile.txt.

    $ curl -I https://example.com

    🔹 Show the HTTP headers from example.com.

    $ curl -X POST -d "name=John&age=30" https://example.com/api

    🔹 Send data to an API using the POST method.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ curl https://example.com

    🔹 Downloads the HTML page from example.com and displays it in the terminal. If you want to save it use the `-O` or `-o` options.
